In this letter, dated July 27, 2014, President Barack Obama informs the Speaker of the House and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate about the temporary relocation of U.S. forces and embassy personnel from Libya due to ongoing violence between Libyan militias near the U.S. Embassy in Tripoli. The U.S. forces and embassy staff were relocated to U.S. bases in Europe via Tunisia. The President states that this action was taken to protect U.S. citizens and in line with his constitutional authority as Commander in Chief. He also mentions that he is providing this report in accordance with the War Powers Resolution. The President expresses his appreciation for the support of Congress in these actions.